h

2
00:00:10,783 --> 00:00:10,899
ht

3
00:00:10,900 --> 00:00:11,017
htt

4
00:00:11,018 --> 00:00:11,135
http

5
00:00:11,136 --> 00:00:11,252
http:

6
00:00:11,253 --> 00:00:11,370
http:/

7
00:00:11,371 --> 00:00:11,488
http://

8
00:00:11,489 --> 00:00:11,605
http://h

9
00:00:11,606 --> 00:00:11,723
http://hi

10
00:00:11,724 --> 00:00:11,840
http://hiq

11
00:00:11,841 --> 00:00:11,958
http://hiqv

12
00:00:11,959 --> 00:00:12,076
http://hiqve

13
00:00:12,077 --> 00:00:12,193
http://hiqve.

14
00:00:12,194 --> 00:00:12,311
http://hiqve.c

15
00:00:12,312 --> 00:00:12,429
http://hiqve.co

16
00:00:12,430 --> 00:00:12,546
http://hiqve.com

17
00:00:12,547 --> 00:00:12,664
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,665 --> 00:00:15,665
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,689 --> 00:00:20,107
<i>Mission accomplished!</i>

20
00:00:20,525 --> 00:00:23,110
<i>Colonel Gascon and his droid squad</i>

21
00:00:23,236 --> 00:00:26,280
<i>steal an encryption module
needed to crack a Separatist code</i>

22
00:00:26,572 --> 00:00:28,950
<i>and stop an impending attack
on the Republic.</i>

23
00:00:29,534 --> 00:00:31,244
<i>After surviving The Void</i>

24
00:00:31,285 --> 00:00:33,871
<i>and escaping the hostile planet of Abafar,</i>

25
00:00:33,955 --> 00:00:37,792
<i>our heroes finally appear to be
headed in the right direction.</i>

26
00:00:44,131 --> 00:00:48,219
Mmm, looks like the Jedi cruiser
is expecting the shuttle.

27
00:00:48,636 --> 00:00:50,555
Well, I'm sure there's someone aboard

28
00:00:50,638 --> 00:00:54,100
who can put this encryption module
to good use.

29
00:00:54,141 --> 00:00:57,395
Well, soldiers,
this is the end of the mission.

30
00:00:57,478 --> 00:00:59,605
Colonel Gascon has succeeded.

31
00:00:59,647 --> 00:01:01,566
Artoo, contact the bridge.

32
00:01:01,649 --> 00:01:04,151
Tell them I request a meal with the captain.

33
00:01:04,277 --> 00:01:06,070
Nothing too fancy,

34
00:01:06,153 --> 00:01:07,655
and I don't eat bantha.

35
00:01:09,490 --> 00:01:12,159
What do you mean,
you still can't make contact?

36
00:01:12,243 --> 00:01:14,829
<i>I have got a bad feeling about this, Colonel.</i>

37
00:01:14,996 --> 00:01:17,456
Something is not right.

38
00:01:22,670 --> 00:01:23,838
<i>Snogwash!</i>

39
00:01:24,005 --> 00:01:26,340
It's probably just the effects of The Void.

40
00:01:26,465 --> 00:01:30,636
All that magnetic disruption
messed up the circuitry.

41
00:01:34,015 --> 00:01:37,059
I will not allow your frivolous worrying

42
00:01:37,184 --> 00:01:40,521
to undermine this glorious moment.

43
00:01:40,730 --> 00:01:42,523
I expect a hero's welcome.

44
00:01:42,648 --> 00:01:46,527
Not to mention my inevitable promotion
to P1 Brigadier.

45
00:02:09,216 --> 00:02:12,887
Wow, they really went overboard
on the welcoming committee.

46
00:02:14,930 --> 00:02:16,557
Good question, Qutee.

47
00:02:16,682 --> 00:02:19,727
Why are there not any other shuttles
or crew members?

48
00:02:19,935 --> 00:02:23,898
Well, everyone's probably preparing to...

49
00:02:24,273 --> 00:02:27,902
Well, they'll all wanna be there
when we break the Separatist code.

50
00:02:30,404 --> 00:02:33,366
How should I know
why all the blast doors are shut?

51
00:02:33,407 --> 00:02:35,576
That's a question
for the captain of this ship.

52
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:40,373
And one I intend to ask
just as soon as I find him.

53
00:02:45,795 --> 00:02:48,297
Sergeant, Colonel Meebur Gascon.

54
00:02:48,547 --> 00:02:50,758
You have no doubt been expecting me.

55
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:54,261
I am delivering the Separatist
encryption module which...

56
00:02:54,762 --> 00:02:58,099
Why, it's just a hologram.

57
00:03:07,775 --> 00:03:10,611
What in the blazes is going on here?

58
00:03:14,323 --> 00:03:17,451
I do not know,
but we just made the jump to hyperspace.

59
00:03:17,535 --> 00:03:20,329
Which means somebody
is navigating this ship.

60
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:35,678
You, droids!
What are you doing on our ship?

61
00:03:36,137 --> 00:03:38,681
Surrender, or you will be destroyed!

62
00:03:38,806 --> 00:03:39,807
Battle droids!

63
00:03:50,234 --> 00:03:53,654
The commander wants the detonator
taken to the control room.

64
00:03:53,696 --> 00:03:54,822
-Roger, roger.
-Roger, roger.

65
00:03:56,490 --> 00:03:59,076
Okay, lift with your legs!
Lift with your legs!

66
00:03:59,160 --> 00:04:02,496
-Okay, balance.
-Watch it! Watch it! Watch it!

67
00:04:02,580 --> 00:04:03,664
-Look out!
-My knees!

68
00:04:03,748 --> 00:04:05,040
Good thinking back there.

69
00:04:05,166 --> 00:04:08,836
But next time, I give the orders.
Understood?

70
00:04:10,045 --> 00:04:12,339
I got it! I got it!

71
00:04:12,923 --> 00:04:14,008
I don't got it!

72
00:04:16,844 --> 00:04:18,012
Uh-oh.

73
00:04:21,515 --> 00:04:24,393
I wasn't programmed for this.

74
00:04:24,894 --> 00:04:27,229
Stop! Which way are we going?

75
00:04:30,524 --> 00:04:31,609
Down here!

76
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,538
Have you seen the intruders?

77
00:04:45,247 --> 00:04:48,042
They went that way? Roger, roger.

78
00:04:52,046 --> 00:04:55,382
My, something very strange
is going on here.

79
00:04:56,050 --> 00:05:00,054
It appears this ship
has been hijacked by Separatists.

80
00:05:02,723 --> 00:05:04,767
What do you mean, it doesn't belong here?

81
00:05:06,101 --> 00:05:09,730
He is right, Colonel.
This is not Republic technology.

82
00:05:09,855 --> 00:05:12,608
Not unless they have
lowered their standards.

83
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:15,236
Well, what exactly do you think it is?

84
00:05:16,946 --> 00:05:18,113
A bomb?

85
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:20,074
What kind of a bomb? Is it armed?

86
00:05:20,199 --> 00:05:22,076
How long do we have? Talk to me!

87
00:05:25,287 --> 00:05:27,581
What do you mean, "The ship is a bomb"?

88
00:05:27,623 --> 00:05:30,084
How can the entire ship be a bomb?

89
00:05:43,764 --> 00:05:45,266
Mother of Kwath.

90
00:05:45,307 --> 00:05:51,313
There must be enough Rhydonium in here
to blow up the entire Republic fleet.

91
00:06:01,782 --> 00:06:06,620
I don't know what any of this means,
but I want off this ship immediately.

92
00:06:08,873 --> 00:06:10,958
My mission is over.

93
00:06:11,625 --> 00:06:14,962
I had no orders to stop Separatist piracy

94
00:06:15,045 --> 00:06:18,424
or disarm massive, titanic-scale bombs.

95
00:06:20,134 --> 00:06:21,802
Ceefor has a good point.

96
00:06:21,969 --> 00:06:24,305
If we do not stop this ship
before it explodes,

97
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:26,640
it could cost the Republic
thousands of lives.

98
00:06:27,141 --> 00:06:29,226
Pure speculation.

99
00:06:29,310 --> 00:06:32,479
We're evacuating this ship,
and that is an order!

100
00:06:36,817 --> 00:06:38,277
Oh, right.

101
00:06:38,319 --> 00:06:42,740
We'll have to wait to evacuate
until the ship is out of hyperspace.

102
00:06:42,823 --> 00:06:44,617
By then, it could be too late.

103
00:06:44,658 --> 00:06:48,579
Once we get where we are going,
my guess is, kaboom!

104
00:07:03,844 --> 00:07:05,429
Wait!

105
00:07:05,512 --> 00:07:07,765
Hey! No!

106
00:07:08,182 --> 00:07:09,642
Okay! Okay!

107
00:07:17,650 --> 00:07:21,320
I don't know, Qutee.
Where's Artoo gone now?

108
00:07:24,990 --> 00:07:27,284
What's going on? Who is this?

109
00:07:28,077 --> 00:07:32,373
I am BNI-393, an LEP servant droid.

110
00:07:32,790 --> 00:07:34,959
My master called me Bunny.

111
00:07:35,292 --> 00:07:37,169
And where is your master?

112
00:07:37,711 --> 00:07:41,131
He was killed when the Separatists
took control of this ship.

113
00:07:41,757 --> 00:07:43,676
Why were you hiding from us?

114
00:07:43,926 --> 00:07:46,345
At first, I did not know if I could trust you.

115
00:07:46,428 --> 00:07:48,973
Then I was not sure you would believe me.

116
00:07:49,056 --> 00:07:50,683
Once you saw the truth,

117
00:07:50,891 --> 00:07:52,643
I was simply hoping
you would abandon ship

118
00:07:53,435 --> 00:07:55,479
and take the rest of us with you.

119
00:07:55,646 --> 00:07:59,900
Rest of you? You're telling me there's
more Republic crew members on board?

120
00:08:04,196 --> 00:08:06,156
Did you destroy the intruders?

121
00:08:06,573 --> 00:08:07,783
No.

122
00:08:08,242 --> 00:08:12,162
There are Republic droids on this ship
that could ruin our plans.

123
00:08:13,747 --> 00:08:17,501
You will search the entire ship
until the intruders are found,

124
00:08:17,584 --> 00:08:19,503
and report back to me.

125
00:08:35,561 --> 00:08:37,062
Is this a joke?

126
00:08:37,312 --> 00:08:39,982
The rest of the crew is in our shuttle?

127
00:08:40,190 --> 00:08:42,234
I told them to wait inside,

128
00:08:42,317 --> 00:08:45,779
and that we would be leaving
as soon as we came out of hyperspace.

129
00:08:54,872 --> 00:08:56,874
You can come out now. It is okay.

130
00:09:05,549 --> 00:09:08,469
These are the other crew members?

131
00:09:08,552 --> 00:09:12,139
As you can see,
none of us can pilot a shuttle.

132
00:09:12,222 --> 00:09:14,141
Which is why we needed you.

133
00:09:14,224 --> 00:09:17,728
Why you need me. Hi, there. I am the pilot.

134
00:09:19,229 --> 00:09:22,900
What is this Separatist plot?
I do not know the details.

135
00:09:22,983 --> 00:09:25,986
I was only able
to steal the coordinates of their target.

136
00:09:26,070 --> 00:09:27,321
Target?

137
00:09:29,406 --> 00:09:32,201
You mean they aren't just planning
to blow up this ship?

138
00:09:32,367 --> 00:09:33,994
I do not believe so.

139
00:09:34,036 --> 00:09:37,498
The coordinates are a space station
in the Corrida system.

140
00:09:37,873 --> 00:09:41,752
What? That's the site
of the Republic Strategy Conference!

141
00:09:44,421 --> 00:09:49,343
How do I know? I was putting the finishing
touches on a report for that conference

142
00:09:49,510 --> 00:09:51,595
when I was assigned this mission.

143
00:09:52,179 --> 00:09:53,722
The Jedi Council will be there,

144
00:09:53,847 --> 00:09:57,017
along with Republic officers
from around the galaxy, and...

145
00:09:57,351 --> 00:09:58,435
What the...

146
00:09:58,519 --> 00:10:01,855
The Separatists are going to ram
the station with this ship!

147
00:10:04,024 --> 00:10:06,860
I agree. We have to do something, Artoo.

148
00:10:06,902 --> 00:10:09,530
See if you can send a transmission
to the Republic

149
00:10:09,571 --> 00:10:10,697
so we can warn them.

150
00:10:10,864 --> 00:10:13,534
It is no use. We have tried that.

151
00:10:13,575 --> 00:10:16,787
All transmissions from this ship
are being blocked.

152
00:10:18,622 --> 00:10:21,708
Hmm. You're right.
We can't just sit here and do nothing.

153
00:10:26,713 --> 00:10:28,590
-Where's he going?
-Uh-oh.

154
00:10:28,882 --> 00:10:30,884
That buzz droid is not with me.

155
00:10:30,968 --> 00:10:32,469
It must be a spy!

156
00:10:33,387 --> 00:10:35,430
Stop that droid!

157
00:11:17,055 --> 00:11:19,057
Where'd he go?
We've got to find him!

158
00:11:19,099 --> 00:11:21,727
I do not know.
I do not see him anywhere.

159
00:11:24,271 --> 00:11:26,148
Colonel, I think I see him.

160
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:29,109
I think I see a whole lot of him.

161
00:11:29,401 --> 00:11:30,444
It's a trap!

162
00:11:57,638 --> 00:12:00,265
Good work!
You've established a perimeter.

163
00:12:00,807 --> 00:12:02,434
There are still more coming.

164
00:12:08,482 --> 00:12:11,318
Please tell me
you have a brilliant strategy, Colonel.

165
00:12:11,443 --> 00:12:13,654
I don't know!
There are just so many of them!

166
00:12:15,155 --> 00:12:16,990
What do you mean, "Get out"?

167
00:12:19,993 --> 00:12:22,663
All right, what are you going to do?

168
00:12:22,788 --> 00:12:25,999
You are going to open the airlock?
Are you crazy, Beezee?

169
00:12:38,804 --> 00:12:41,473
Everybody, magnetize your feet!
Lock down!

170
00:12:45,102 --> 00:12:46,937
Beezee, magnetize!

171
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:48,105
Magnetize!

172
00:12:48,689 --> 00:12:49,815
No!

173
00:13:00,450 --> 00:13:04,371
Artoo, close the door! Close the door!

174
00:13:14,965 --> 00:13:16,341
Poor Beezee.

175
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:19,678
You will be missed, soldier.

176
00:13:20,137 --> 00:13:21,888
Artoo is right.

177
00:13:21,972 --> 00:13:26,226
Colonel, would you say something
to honor his heroic sacrifice?

178
00:13:26,810 --> 00:13:29,062
I suppose that's appropriate.

179
00:13:29,187 --> 00:13:32,232
I'll have to make it quick,
because we don't have much time.

180
00:13:32,649 --> 00:13:36,236
When this D Squad started our mission,
I had doubts,

181
00:13:36,528 --> 00:13:40,490
grave doubts, that we would ever survive,
let alone succeed.

182
00:13:40,699 --> 00:13:42,492
But we worked together.

183
00:13:42,659 --> 00:13:43,910
We didn't give up hope.

184
00:13:44,036 --> 00:13:46,580
We showed courage in the face of death.

185
00:13:47,164 --> 00:13:51,835
It shocks me to say this,
but we make an excellent team!

186
00:13:51,918 --> 00:13:55,672
Now we've lost
one of our members, Beezee.

187
00:13:56,048 --> 00:14:00,844
But we must remember,
Beezee sacrificed himself for us.

188
00:14:01,178 --> 00:14:03,889
That's what a good soldier
does sometimes.

189
00:14:05,015 --> 00:14:09,102
The only way to honor that sacrifice
is to stop this ship

190
00:14:09,227 --> 00:14:12,689
and prevent the Separatists
from taking any more Republic lives.

191
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,609
Are you with me?

192
00:14:22,324 --> 00:14:24,826
Have the buzz droids reported back in yet?

193
00:14:25,035 --> 00:14:27,871
No, there has been no signal from them.

194
00:14:27,954 --> 00:14:31,208
In fact, I cannot even locate
their signal anymore.

195
00:14:31,291 --> 00:14:34,461
We must assume, then,
that the buzz droids have failed.

196
00:14:34,544 --> 00:14:38,215
I want those intruders found
before they ruin our plans.

197
00:14:38,632 --> 00:14:40,300
-Roger, roger.
-Roger, roger.

198
00:14:44,721 --> 00:14:46,640
All right, everybody knows the plan?

199
00:14:46,723 --> 00:14:50,310
We get the injured droids to the shuttle
and distract the battle droids

200
00:14:50,394 --> 00:14:54,773
while Artoo goes up to the detonator
and programs it to explode early.

201
00:14:54,856 --> 00:14:56,983
Hopefully, he can make it back
to the shuttle,

202
00:14:57,067 --> 00:14:59,653
and we can all get off the ship
before it blows up.

203
00:15:01,405 --> 00:15:03,031
Good luck, Artoo!

204
00:15:07,202 --> 00:15:09,287
The intruders! Destroy them!

205
00:15:25,220 --> 00:15:28,432
You can make it! Hurry! Hurry!

206
00:15:49,619 --> 00:15:51,246
We have our target in sight.

207
00:15:51,997 --> 00:15:54,583
Full ahead. Ramming speed.

208
00:15:55,083 --> 00:15:57,461
Evacuation plan is now underway.

209
00:15:58,170 --> 00:16:01,256
I will go to the detonator
and start the countdown.

210
00:16:13,101 --> 00:16:17,272
The worst part about our job
are these boring strategy conferences.

211
00:16:17,731 --> 00:16:18,773
Cheer up, Anakin.

212
00:16:18,940 --> 00:16:22,903
This is your chance to voice all your
complaints about military protocol.

213
00:16:22,986 --> 00:16:25,697
And it looks as though
we can finally get underway.

214
00:16:25,780 --> 00:16:28,909
I will inform Master Windu
the last straggler has arrived,

215
00:16:28,992 --> 00:16:31,536
while you work on your attitude.

216
00:16:35,665 --> 00:16:38,168
Isn't that ship coming in a little too fast?

217
00:16:42,631 --> 00:16:43,715
There's the shuttle!

218
00:16:50,472 --> 00:16:52,474
Careful !
You'll hit the Rhydonium!

219
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:54,726
Everyone, head to the ship!

220
00:16:54,809 --> 00:16:56,603
Ceefor and I will distract them.

221
00:17:15,330 --> 00:17:16,873
You are too late.

222
00:17:19,918 --> 00:17:22,170
Once the detonation sequence
has commenced,

223
00:17:22,254 --> 00:17:24,256
there is no stopping it.

224
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:31,096
Now let's see if Artoo made it
to the detonator.

225
00:17:39,062 --> 00:17:41,565
Artoo is in trouble! Come on!

226
00:17:44,776 --> 00:17:47,445
Artoo will never make it back
to the shuttle in time!

227
00:17:47,529 --> 00:17:49,698
We've got to delay the launch!

228
00:17:52,951 --> 00:17:54,953
The cruiser has not slowed its pace.

229
00:17:55,328 --> 00:17:56,871
Have you been able
to contact their captain?

230
00:17:58,081 --> 00:18:00,750
Zeenine says he cannot make contact
with anyone.

231
00:18:01,126 --> 00:18:03,545
Where's Artoo when I need him?

232
00:18:14,014 --> 00:18:16,600
We've got to regroup
and head back for Artoo.

233
00:18:17,809 --> 00:18:19,644
Well, we're changing the plan!

234
00:18:19,686 --> 00:18:21,271
No one gets left behind!

235
00:18:21,354 --> 00:18:24,190
And we're not leaving until I say so.

236
00:18:24,691 --> 00:18:26,026
<i>Prepare for liftoff!</i>

237
00:18:48,548 --> 00:18:50,383
No, it is too soon.

238
00:18:50,884 --> 00:18:53,303
We are scanning a large amount
of Rhydonium on that ship.

239
00:18:53,637 --> 00:18:54,679
It's a bomb!

240
00:19:31,758 --> 00:19:33,885
And you thought this conference
would be boring.

241
00:19:38,765 --> 00:19:39,933
Mayday! Mayday!

242
00:19:40,058 --> 00:19:43,228
Space station <i>Valor,</i>
this is Colonel Meebur Gascon!

243
00:19:43,603 --> 00:19:44,729
<i>Can anyone hear me?</i>

244
00:19:45,772 --> 00:19:48,066
We read you, Colonel.
This is General Skywalker.

245
00:19:48,108 --> 00:19:49,442
What's going on out there?

246
00:19:49,776 --> 00:19:52,070
Slight change in our mission, General.

247
00:19:52,112 --> 00:19:55,031
The droids and I
were stowaways on that cruiser.

248
00:19:55,115 --> 00:19:56,241
Where's Artoo?

249
00:19:56,282 --> 00:20:00,453
I'm sorry to report he was on that ship
when it blew up, sir.

250
00:20:00,954 --> 00:20:03,081
He just saved all your lives.

251
00:20:03,415 --> 00:20:06,084
I want a salvage team out there, now!

252
00:20:06,292 --> 00:20:07,419
Yes, sir!

253
00:20:38,825 --> 00:20:39,951
Artoo!

254
00:20:42,829 --> 00:20:44,706
You made it, buddy!

255
00:20:44,831 --> 00:20:46,541
Hey, you're a big hero!

256
00:20:49,502 --> 00:20:51,671
There's someone here
who wants to speak to you.

257
00:20:57,510 --> 00:21:01,181
R2-D2, are we glad to see you.

258
00:21:01,347 --> 00:21:02,682
I am most glad.

259
00:21:02,807 --> 00:21:05,018
Quiet, WAC, I'm talking here.

260
00:21:05,143 --> 00:21:06,186
Yes, sir, Colonel.

261
00:21:08,813 --> 00:21:12,150
In truth, I might just be a map reader,

262
00:21:12,192 --> 00:21:15,570
and I don't have much battle experience,

263
00:21:15,695 --> 00:21:20,408
but, Artoo, you are the bravest droid
I have ever met.

264
00:21:20,533 --> 00:21:21,576
You all are!

265
00:21:22,202 --> 00:21:26,748
I would be proud to serve with you droids
anytime, anywhere!

266
00:21:26,873 --> 00:21:29,542
Oh, I am glad to hear you say that, Colonel,

267
00:21:29,584 --> 00:21:32,921
because I hear we have been assigned
to the same platoon.

268
00:21:33,046 --> 00:21:37,425
We will be seeing each other every day
for the rest of the war!

269
00:21:37,550 --> 00:21:40,011
That's great, WAC.

270
00:21:42,204 --> 00:21:47,204
http://hiqve.com/

